    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>Hobson writes to confirm that she would like The Hogarth Press to publish her book and also suggests the title: 'Smoke Rings'
                   Handwritten letter signed by Hobson
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
    <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                <placeName><choice><abbr>w.e.l.<expan>West East London</expan></abbr></choice></placeName>
                    <date when="1924-03-04">March 4 24</date>
                </dateline>
                <address>
                    <addrLine><persName>Leonard Woolf</persName></addrLine>
                    <addrLine> 56 Cartwright Gardens</addrLine>
                </address>
                <salute>Dear sir,</salute>
            </opener>
        <p>
            I thank you for your letter of the
            <lb/>
            1st month and would confirm that I
            <lb/>
            would like you to publish the book for
            <lb/>
            me on the terms which you support:
            <lb/>
        </p>
        <p>
            I take it therefore that you will
            <lb/>
            now prepare a formal entrant which I
            <lb/>
            shall be glad to recieve at your convenience.
            <lb/>
        </p>
        <p>
            I also thank you for your specimen <gap reason="illegible" extent="1"/>
            <lb/>
            which appears to me to be satisfactory,
            <lb/>
            and which I now return
            <lb/>
        </p>
        <p>
            I suggest as a little fun little book <lb/>
            "Smoke Rings" <lb/>
        </p>
        <closer>
        <salute>Yours faithfully,</salute>
        <signed>Coralie Hobson</signed>
        </closer>
        </div>
    </body>
    </text>
